This paper discusses the impact of processing resource sharing on the placement of Virtual Network Functions (VNFs) in a Service Function Chain (SFC) to meet the performance requirements. This topic falls under the area of network function virtualization (NFV) and network infrastructure (NI), making cs.NI the most likely sub-category. The paper also considers the latency requirements of SFCs, which falls under the area of systems and control (SY), making cs.SY another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the consolidation of VNFs to reduce capital expenditures, which relates to the area of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (DC), making cs.DC another possible sub-category. The paper also evaluates the impact of processing resource sharing on the performance of VNFs, which falls under the area of architecture (AR) and programming languages (PL), making cs.AR and cs.PL other possible sub-categories.
